Date: Sun, 22 Feb 2004 20:04:36 +0000
From: Nick Collins <nc272
Subject: [livecode] an angle to cut out iTunes?


Alex's comment on code running in the mind of the programmer (from the OS 
paper) is probably quite pertinent. Also to remember are the continuums of 
interaction (power of controls with respect to parameter space of music?) 
and of gestural content, particularly directness of expressive detail- 
no-one can code with haptic rate timing deviations for expressivity...

live coding allows the exploration of abstract algorithm spaces as an 
intellectual improvisation.

thought experiment- someone writes down an instruction list for their use 
of iTunes. They proceed to HDJ according to this instruction set. But 
halfway through they modify the list.

Was that live coding?

We'll probably always be a bit stuck facing the continuum. But we can 
encourage rather than demand- so that common sense prevails. Profundity of 
change and depth of insight into code and dmusic representation to be 
applauded.
N

