Date: Thu, 6 May 2004 08:45:55 +0100 (BST)
Subject: paper
From: "alex" <alex


Hi TOPLAP,

Happily, we had our paper accepted to the READ_ME software art festival.

The festival is in two parts; the "Software Art and Cultures" conference
from 23rd to 24th August and the "runme-dorkbot city camp" from 25th to
27th August.

http://readme.runme.org/

The paper is accepted for the conference part.  It would be nice if we
could do some kind of workshop, collaborations, demonstrations and some
performances as part of the citycamp part.

If you can make it, please register for the runme part now.  There's
free accommodation and money available for travel too.  It's all
explained on the registration form.

It would be fantastic to present our ideas at the academic conference
and develop them further during the citycamp.

Anyway, due to some mix-ups with the paper we haven't got much time to
write it.  It needs to be ready for printing by 1st June!  What makes
this worse is that Ade and I are also collaborating on another paper for
the conference, about generative art.

What ideas do we want to get across in this paper?  Who wants to help
write it?  How should we structure and write it?

alex











