Date: Thu, 02 Sep 2004 17:15:51 +0100
From: Nick Collins <nc272
Subject: Re: [livecode] live coding and slashdot


Here's my favourite comment from that thread, which perhaps highlights the 
danger of having just a little knowledge:

Real men use CSOUND for "programmed music" :)

Seriously, csound is designed as a programming language for music and is 
phenominally powerful and can be used in real time. If I were hacking code 
for music onstage, that is what I would use. Having said that, I'd rather 
use my guitar or synth(s) as they are the ultimate in "live composition" 
instruments...


