Ok, the wiki started to get spam again.

It could well be people doing it by hand, but in case it's robots, I
hacked in some anti-robot code.  Now you have to type a passcode before
submitting a change.  Apologies to those with poor eyesight and screen
readers :(

Also there's some TOPLAPpery coming up in London on Thursday and in
Huddersfield on Friday and Saturday.  That's
http://www.no-signal.net/xtns4/ and http://ultrasound.ws/ .

I'm currently helping to promote the London gig, which features NeboGeo
(Dave), Klippav (Nick and Fredrik), and TabLex (French Alex and I)  so
please pass the following infos around...

Seeya!

alex


Bleeding edge performances at state51 extension #4
at state51, London E2, United Kingdom
this Thursday 25th November, from 7pm (first band 8pm)

Door tax: 5 (2 discount for those who email alex@hiddenorg!)

 event info: http://www.no-signal.net/xtns4/
        map: http://streetmap.co.uk/streetmap.dll?Postcode2Map?code=e2+7ef
TOPLAP info: http://toplap.org/


A chance to see a whole bunch of TOPLAP affiliates in London before
they travel up for the Ultrasound festival this weekend
[http://ultrasound.ws/]


TabLex
------
Processed drums, software chopping up and restructuring live drumming
into fractured, impossible rhythms, vs live coded Perl generating
wigged-out skiffle.  Very live, improvised computer music.


Klippav
-------
Feed your bodies with klippav's live synced beat and video cuts.  Live
coded generative breaks feedbacking through live processed feeds of
dancing ducks.  These tightly controlled visuals and sonics create
body-rocking and mind-blowing intensity.


Nebogeo
-------
Live coded evolution, witness algorithms corrupt and breed with your
own eyes and ears.  A solo performance of experiments on real
artificial creatures, taking them (and us) on a journey into boundless
recursion.


Also showing: Kapitol band 1 and Dean Roberts

See http://www.no-signal.net/xtns4/ for full information.

This has been a TOPLAP communication.  state51 extension #4 is in
collaboration with and organised by no_signal .



