Date: Wed, 01 Dec 2004 23:03:51 +0000
From: Nick Collins <nc272
Subject: Re: [livecode] toplap at club transmediale


Jan at transmediale sent through the following info, which I'm passing on 
and throwing open to some discussion.

They want a proposal in next few days which we can prepare openly, probably 
using the wiki to help.

I enclose my questions and his responses.

Various of you have expressed interest. We are also investigating an 
off-transmediale event so that lots of people can play and no-one is missed 
out.

For our proposal, there are many possibilties- there could be an official 
TOPLAP jam as the main performance, or a live cinema thing with 
Julian/Alberto.
Talk/demoes could be Julian/Alberto, Chuck etc...

We can also hold informal talks I'm sure on the side. Seems like a good 
excuse for a big TOPLAP meeting anyhow.

There are some fees from ultrasound/state51 we hope to put towards 
expenses, we have Fredrik's flat (thanks f) etc. So even though Jan prefers 
covering 3-4 people below we can fly and accommodate more than this.

Anyway, thoughts, preferences for nature of involvement? Quotes for 
expenses?
Cheers
N


> how much time would be allotted to a performance or talk? For discussion
> amongst TOPLAP members about who would like to do what, this would be very
> helpful. I assume for live performance you mean a maximum of two distinct
> artists? Or is there a certain time limit and we can share that amongst a
> group of performers?

