Subject: Re: [livecode] toplap at club transmediale
From: alex <alex
Date: Sat, 04 Dec 2004 22:06:29 +0000



As I say in the wiki, I'd favour a collaborative workshop, with several
informal talks, 20 mins each max plus plenty of Q&A and discussion.  I
don't think half a day is enough for a tutorial style workshop, and it
seems a shame to base it on a single toplap approach.  I think this
would fit better with transmediale, where participants might be more
interested in the nature of live coding than in learning a live
programming environment, at least while they are at the festival.

