>Dear Andreas,
>
>Hope all is well with you. 
>
>I'm writing to tell you briefly about TOPLAP and our plans for
>transmediale, and to ask your advice.
>
>We at TOPLAP (Transnational Organisation for Promotion of Live Algorithm
>Programming) have charged ourselves with the exploration and promotion
>of live algorithms - that is algorithms that can be edited while they
>are executing.  We project our screens during performances so that the
>audience may see the sourcecode of the software that is generating the
>music and/or video, as it is written and manipulated.
>
>More information about past performances, papers, our manifesto etc can
>be found at http://toplap.org/
>
>We're very pleased to have our proposal for (club) transmediale 2005
>accepted, and are piecing together a plan.  Jan Rohlf has asked us to
>conduct a half day workshop, group performance and participate in a
>talk/panel session.  We've also been in contact with c-base (who you
>introduced Saul and I to last year), hopefully we'll be able to organise
>with them a further evening of performances by TOPLAP members.
>
>Now on to the problems.  There are ten TOPLAP members who would like to
>participate in these proceedings, and it would be great for us to have
>as many people there as possible, many of us haven't yet met each other
>face to face.  Here we are:
>
>* Fredik Olofsson (berlin)
>* Kristjan Varnik (berlin)
>* Julian Rohrhuber (de)
>* Alberto de Campo (de)
>* Nick Collins (uk)
>* Dave Griffiths (uk)
>* Ade Ward (uk)
>* Alex McLean (uk)
>* Amy Alexander (us)
>* Ge Wang (us)
>
>Of course club transmediale can help with travel for some of us, but
>only 3 or 4.  Also you can see that four of us are based in Germany, two
>will be in Berlin.  So the big cost is with bringing Amy Alexander and
>Ge Wang over.  We estimate that return flights from the US to Berlin
>will be around 408 euros per person.
>
>We have raised 700 euros in donations from TOPLAP performance and
>presentation fees, but think we need another 400-500 euros on top of
>that to get everyone to transmediale.
>
>So I have two things to ask - firstly if we were to hold an event at
>c-base one evening during transmediale, could that be affiliated to
>transmediale as with the dorkbot last year?
>
>Secondly, do you have ideas for how we might find the missing money for
>travel expenses?  Perhaps there are still other areas in which we can
>get involved with a bit more funding.  Any suggestions or help would be
>much appreciated.
>
>Take care and best wishes,
>
>alex


--=-J3Yzng/ZmoCmgTm5xeOY--


