This sounds really good.  Somehow I didn't anticipate the 600 euro fee,
that will be handy!  It seems fairest to put the 600 euros into the
collective travel pot.  We need to look over the finances again, but
this is starting to look good.  Please continue looking for funding
though Amy and Ge, the next job is to try to get Craig over, and pay for
a TOPLAP dinner...

How do people feel about the full day workshop?  I'm only worried about
the lack of continuity but with so many people around to show their
stuff...

Down sides that I see from a first reading...  Only two people from the
UK, but I guess that is the best offer they can make, we asked if they
could stretch it to three.  It doesn't mention festival passes - we
should ask if we can have passes for all of us.  Is there anything I've
missed?

How does this programme look?

Friday - Transmediale starts, some people arrive, go and party at club
transmediale
Saturday - Everyone else arrives, maybe a TOPLAP dinner and planning,
then more partying
Sunday - Presentation led by Amy (mini panel style) and live jam at club
transmediale
Monday - workshop at transmediale (Haus der Kulturen der Welt), perhaps
half led by Ge and the other half led by Julian?
Tuesday - possible participation in a panel session with one person from
TOPLAP, then evening performances at c-base
Wednesday - Go home

Exciting!



Date: Tue, 7 Dec 2004 21:03:21 -0800 (PST)
From: Amy Alexander <amy
Subject: Re: AW: AW: [livecode] toplap at club transmediale


On Tue, 7 Dec 2004, alex wrote:

a> How do people feel about the full day workshop?  I'm only worried about
a> the lack of continuity but with so many people around to show their
a> stuff...
a> 

i'm not sure what you mean by lack of continuity? i think it roughly 
sounds good, though my first impression is it might be trying to fit too 
much into the relatively short talk/panel and then we could have possibly 
more time for the workshops than we want.

i'm not sure how the workshops would be structured: are they supposed to 
be instructional? since they're also supposed to be for a general 
audience, i'd think it would be tough to actually teach much about most of 
the apps - on the other hand, 2 half-day sessions is a bit long for just 
general discussion - though having a lot of apps and authors will 
certainly help with that.

so perhaps we should emphasize the conceptual discussion in the talk/panel 
and keep discussion of each tool very short - i.e. discussing each app in 
the context of the author's particular interest/reasaons/opinions about 
livecoding... thus hopefully whetting appetites for interested folks to 
come to the workshops. then present the tools in more depth at the 
workshops. how does that sound? one downside of that is i guess the 
workshops are limited attendance and may have to be booked in advance of 
the talk/panel.


a> Down sides that I see from a first reading...  Only two people from the
a> UK, but I guess that is the best offer they can make, we asked if they
a> could stretch it to three.  It doesn't mention festival passes - we
a> should ask if we can have passes for all of us.  Is there anything I've
a> missed?
a> 

i can't think of anything else but let's definitely ask for festival 
passes for all of us! 

a> How does this programme look?
a> 

looks good to me!
-@



