Date: Wed, 15 Dec 2004 09:36:17 +0000
From: Nick Collins <nc272
Subject: [livecode] live algorithms network


just a brief report:

I attended the live algorithms network meeting over the last two days: the 
focus wqs on autonomous AI performers for improvisation. So a complementary 
strand of research to TOPLAP, no real clash of ideology, the two are 
different in aim (though a few issues may overlap, ie demonstrating the 
intentionality of algorithms when your algorithms lack human expressions : 
) ).

The AI agent aspect was not exhibited particularly well by last night's 
concert, with some relatively typical electronic music performances (but 
some nice ones, and good to hear Jonathon Impett's emergent music system).

cheers all,
N
    


From: "Dave Griffiths" <dave
Subject: Re: [livecode] airfares going up
Date: Wed, 15 Dec 2004 10:55:35 +0100


On Tue, 14 Dec 2004 17:39:05 +0000, alex wrote
