sure thing - my whole live music setup is now on savannah cvs:
https://savannah.nongnu.org/projects/livenoisetools
and I even have a user or two now learning score code! :)

but it's probably easier to show fluxus, as the relationship between the code
and the artwork is a bit clearer - and it uses a proper script language. Let
me know what you need in terms of example scripts and documentation.

I should also have notified the list, but I did a sneaky fluxus performance
last night at the end of the Mute "Open Source Software Workshop" while Chun
Lee (http://www.sonicvariable.com/) provided music from his pd setup. I think
most people there were a bit dazed from two days of intensive pd hacking to
really get into it, bit it did spark some interesting conversation in the pub
afterward...

such as live collaberative coding over the net with some sort of source code
repository software (such as cvs) hacked for faster edits. This would make
network jamming a lot easier as you'd only have to distribute the code. Is
this audicle territory?

cheers,

dave


