> did we send this one yet or do we still need to?
>

We have this so far: (http://www.toplap.org/?node=Transmediale2005)

For the live jam, we probably won't all fit on stage at the same time, 
although it would be fun to try. We should structure it carefully and be 
careful that it doesn't resort to pure noise (until the end). A rehearsal 
would be great.

We'll get three data projectors overlayed on one screen. Amy could bring a 
'video jockey' to switch between performers, operated by whoever isn't 
performing at that moment, to allow more people to perform than there are 
projectors.

We'll need M-F VGA cables (i.e. VGA extension cables) - one per concurrent 
performer using the video jockey. The video jockey can accomodate eight 
computers.

Alex will bring a small ten channel audio mixer, another stage mixer will 
be provided by club transmediale.


---------------

So I think we need to draw something up specific to their stressed out 
requirements. I think Amy/Fredrik you were discussing on this list already 
for projection. for audio, I assume there won't be more than five audio 
outs at once? me, Alex, Ade, Fredrik, Ge, Craig, Kristjan, Julian, 
Alberto...hmmmmm, make that ten. I think we better request six stereo ins 
to their mixer (one for Alex's mixer plus five to cover us).


