Date: Mon, 24 Jan 2005 18:24:41 -0800 (PST)
From: Amy Alexander <amy
Subject: [livecode] more on video switches


i picked up a KVM switch over the weekend to test out with projector. 
(hope to return if we don't need.) 
unfortunately as i suspected, it's not possible to leave a port vacant to 
use as "black" (no sync so the projector starts searching for input). on 
the other hand, a computer hooked up to it with a blank screensaver works 
reasonably well as a "black" signal. so, if we want to, we could:

a) have several people hooked up on projector A to the "real" switch as 
planned
b) have 2 people on one of the other blended projectors (call it 
"B") alternate playing. 
whoever is not playing would leave their computer there running a blank 
screensaver, but set not to go into standby.
c) when we want to eliminate chaos, switch the display on projector B to 
the "blank" computer. performer on projector B can continue playing audio, 
but their screen won't be seen.
d) in order to balance things out, we can also black out projector "A" 
sometimes (the switch there has a black position on it automatically.)

the KVM switch i picked up also unfortunately requires a ps/2 keyboard - 
has no manual switch. i wouldn't like to haul another keyboard with me 
(i'm bringing one or 2 of my usb portables already), though somewhere at 
home i have a flexible rubber keyboard i might be able to bring if i can 
find it. though if there's a ps/2 keyboard someone can bring from berlin, 
that'd be nice.

or: if this all seems too complicated, we could just forget about it and 
have all images supered. i'm just a bit concerned because 2 images for the 
whole show wouldn't be too bad, but 3 the whole time could look a bit 
chaotic.

thoughts?


-@



