From: Signwave UK <mail
Subject: [livecode] [pr] Signwave Pure Events
Date: Thu, 24 Mar 2005 17:54:13 +0000



Friday 25th March 2005
London, England
FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE - WITH APOLOGIES FOR CROSS-POSTING


Signwave now accepting beta testers for new generative audio software 
used at 2005 World Expo.


Signwave UK, makers of generative software artworks such as Autoshop 
and Auto-Illustrator, are now accepting applicants to join the beta 
testing phase for their latest generative audio software, Pure Events, 
which will be pre-released in the first half of 2005 for Mac OS X 10.3 
or higher.

By combining radical practices such as DSP programming, module 
tracking, spreadsheet calculations and livecoding, Pure Events makes it 
possible to create generative music and audio systems that change in 
exciting and dynamic ways at runtime. This "never-the-same-twice" 
technique, ideal for realtime ambient soundtracks as well as live 
musical performances, has garnered considerable attention in the arts 
and media industries recently. In 2001, Signwave won the Transmediale 
Artistic Software award for their generative vector graphics 
application, Auto-Illustrator. Now they turn their attention to music 
and audio production, and plan to encourage diverse exploration and 
creation of audio systems via this exciting new piece of software.

Signwave Pure Events is currently powering the ambient soundtrack in 
the UK Pavilion at the 2005 World Expo in Aichi, Japan. Accompanying 
the interactive exhibits on site, Pure Events composites fragments of 
both synthetic and sampled sounds, and is responsible for generating a 
surround-sound atmosphere to complement the theme of this year's Expo: 
nature.

Individuals interested in joining the beta testing program for Pure 
Events can enrol at http://www.pure-events.com/

For more information on Signwave, their products and services, or to 
contact them, please visit http://www.signwave.co.uk/

More information on the UK Pavilion at the 2005 World Expo can be found 
at http://www.my-earth.org.uk/



