Hi All,

Just a quick note to let the list know that Live Coding is happening =20
in Australia.=A0 This is the best of a bad bunch of photo's of Andrew =20=

Sorensen and Andrew Brown performing last thursday at =20
the=A0Australasian Computer Music Conference in Brisbane. (me on the =20
left and AB on the right).  We're coding in a new environment called =20
impromptu.  Impromptu is a scheme interpreter closely coupled to a =20
synthesis/scheduling engine (AiME).  I'll pass around links to =20
impromptu as soon as it is stable enough for public consumption.

Cheers :)

Andrew Sorensen.



