Date: Sat, 23 Jul 2005 09:53:47 +0100
From: Nick Collins <nc272
Subject: [livecode] CAIGUI


Composers Against Intermediate (Graphical/Gestural User) Interfaces

Julian and I were perhaps a little drunk but invented a new group (name 
unsettled as yet) which would promote TOPLAP's pure performance algorithm 
writing at one end of its remit and pure machine listening/ensemble playing 
from audio input or motion tracking devices only at the other end, and 
nothing in between.

We hate widgets, slider banks, virtual cables and all interfacing gimmicks 
without neuroscientific basis.

Write textual arcana, or work as a traditional musician linked to computers 
by automatic tracking systems only.



