Date: Thu, 29 Sep 2005 10:08:53 +0100
From: Nick Collins <nc272
Subject: [livecode] The Glass Bead Game


out of curiosity, has anyone else read Hermann Hesse's Glass Bead Game book =

recently, interpreting it in the light of live coding?

Hermann Hesse The Glass Bead Game, Vintage: London 2000 translated by=20
Richard and Clara Winston.

P23 GBG as live coding, description of the game

>From stringing beads on wire to represent musical notation, =91was taken =
over=20
by mathematicians.=92

P23-4 =91the players, mutually elaborating these processes, threw these=20
abstract formulas at one another, displaying the sequences and=20
possibilities of their science.=92

Mnemonists spoil the game
P70 =91talent without character, virtuosity without values=92
introduce contemplation (spirituality)

Physicalist position p81 =91someone who can read notes but has no command =
of=20
my instrument should not join in the dialogue on music.=92

A public essay on algorithm. A disputation/dialectic.
P101, doubt of game. =91It would be better not to play this Game, but to=20
occupy oneself with uncontaminated mathematics and good music.=92




