Date: Mon, 17 Apr 2006 12:48:04 +0200
From: =?ISO-8859-1?Q?Atte_Andr=E9_Jensen?= <atte.jensen
Subject: [livecode] Introduction + question


Hi

I'm new here, so let me introduce myself.

I'm mainly a jazz pianist, but also a keyboard player and linux user. 
The last 3 years almost all my keyboard playing has been with my laptop 
running csound, controlled with 3 usb keyboards.

Over the last year I got increasingly interrested in livecoding, first 
by discovering livenoisetools and mondrian, later by looking at chuck.

Now for an initial question:

I'd like to keep using csound, since I know it very well, and build 
quite a lot of instruments over the years. The last few days I've been 
playing with mondrian together with csound, and some aspects of it work 
quite well. For instance I realy like the idea of expressing melodies in 
relative terms + the ability to put a small motif into a macro, put more 
motif-macros into themes, etc.

However, it seems that mondrian is more geared towards composing, and 
I'm looking for a live oriented tool. Something that'll let me interact 
with it via midi keyboards, and that'll output midi events I can route 
to csound.

Any recomendations for software that'll do that?

-- 
peace, love & harmony
Atte

http://www.atte.dk
http://www.atte.dk/gps


