Hi Folks,

On 16/04/2006, at 8:04 AM, alex wrote:

> So we have some new members, please introduce yourselves - what are  
> you
> livecoding and why?  Or if you're not livecoding right now, why not?

My introduction to the list.

I've been involved with computer music for some time and a bunch the  
recent activity surrounding this is focused on adaptive music systems  
and is documented, along with some colleagues, here http:// 
adaptivemusic.net/

My live coding activities are done in conjunction with Andrew  
Sorensen and some documentation of our work and Andrew's live coding  
environment called Impromptu are found here http:// 
impromptu.moso.com.au/.

I'm looking forward to continued interesting discussion on this list.

Cheers,

Andrew Brown
