Date: Sun, 23 Apr 2006 16:42:37 +0200
From: Marcel Wierckx <Marcel
Subject: Re: [livecode] new members


hello Livecoders

High time to introduce myself lest I drift into the obscurity of lurkers.

I'm a composer who also makes video art, mostly=20
for theater and dance but I also do a lot of=20
autonomous work. I've also acted and danced in=20
some small stage productions, and I make=20
installation art and write software too. And in=20
the little time left over I teach music=20
technology and composition at the Utrecht School=20
of Music Technology. If you want you can read all=20
about me at http://www.LowNorth.nl/marcel/ (allow=20
me to apologize in advance for the cheesy=20
picture).

So that all the purists can dismiss me=20
immediately: I do live coding with MaxMSP.

My approach to live coding is a little less=20
technical than it is conceptual. I'm a big fan of=20
the early surrealists, and my goal is to apply=20
the idea of "=E9criture automatique" to live=20
coding. For the (few) performances I've done with=20
my students we set a time limit - 5 minutes -=20
within which the performer has to put together a=20
generative patch.
A small Max patch running in the background=20
crashes the computer after exactly 5 minutes of=20
coding. This not only heightens the level of=20
stress the performer experiences, resulting in a=20
more invigorating experience for everybody, but=20
it also ensures that the performer's work can't=20
be saved, reflecting the transient (volatile?)=20
nature of the medium.

Anyone living in the Netherlands is of course welcome to see us perform:

Monday 15 May at Kraakgeluiden in Amsterdam (http://www.kraakgeluiden.com/)

=46riday 9 June at Kikker Theater in Utrecht (as=20
part of the "SuperProeflokaal" event)
http://www.theaterkikker.nl/muziek.php?id=3D577&agenda=3Ddetail

thanks for your bandwidth

Marcel

