Date: Tue, 25 Apr 2006 11:17:54 -0700
From: Craig Latta <craig
Subject: [livecode] re: livecode -> midi



	Nick writes:

 > ...I think both Quoth (Craig Latta) and fluxus/noisepattern (Dave
 > Griffiths) use MIDI out to software synths.

	Yes, I use Quoth[1] with both internal and external MIDI devices. It's 
written with Squeak Smalltalk[2], another system which seems perfectly 
suited to livecoding (because of its dynamism and reflection). Quoth 
makes extensive use of runtime code generation (English-to-Smalltalk) 
and context manipulation (a la continuations and exceptions).

	There's an OSC package available for Squeak, as I recall.

	For those in the San Francisco Bay Area, I'm giving a presentation 
about Quoth at the monthly SF Dorkbot[3] meeting tomorrow (oops, sorry 
for the short notice).


-C

[1] http://netjam.org/quoth
[2] http://squeak.org
[3] http://dorkbot.org/dorkbotsf

-- 
Craig Latta
improvisational musical informaticist
www.netjam.org
Smalltalkers do: [:it | All with: Class, (And love: it)]




