Hello everyone,

Sorry it's taken me so long to get around to my introduction. Things  
are pretty busy for me at the moment since the end of the semester is  
approaching.

I'm Mark Egli and I'm currently working on a Computer Engineering BS  
degree at the University of Illinois.

I'm not livecoding because my forays into programming thus far have  
been rather limited and I find the list of Toplap Systems to be  
rather daunting. Nonetheless, I have more than a passing interest in  
algorithmic composition so I'm here the glean as much information as  
possible. I'm also interested in trying to pick up knowledge along  
these lines in an academic setting, but I haven't been able to find  
much available here at the U of I. If anyone wants to make a pitch  
for their college/university, I might be looking at grad school  
options sooner than I'd like to think about.

-M


