Date: Mon, 01 May 2006 21:31:47 +0200
From: Peter Plessas <plessas
Subject: Re: [livecode] new members


Hi all,

time to say hello from Graz/Austria. I don't know if PureData (and other 
patcher languages) do suffice the toplap manifesto, but we are happy 
using pd in a performance called "blind date" where we approach the live 
coding/audience challenge by using two computers, one making audio, the 
other video/3D. Both screens with the patches are displayed as well.
We take live-coding to another level by letting two people work on the 
same box, using two sets of mice, keyboards and monitors, to allow 
collaborative patching where one has to allow the other to program as 
well,plus making changes to what your partner has already done on screen.
In the recent version of this performance setup, more people than 
computers were available, so we would make a change every 5 minutes, 
resulting in the player sitting in front of a fresh patch, unknown so 
far to himself, struggling with the way to add/modify it.
We see this as a quite promising way to do live-coding, collaborative 
patching, and audience interaction at the same time.

Photos: http://pd-graz.mur.at/concerts/blinddate?b_start:int=10

happy to see this list coming up!

regards,

Peter


