Date: Tue, 6 Jun 2006 11:47:39 +0200
From: douglas edric stanley <destanley
Subject: Re: [livecode] Doug Stanley interview


>I thought I'd comment in the livecode mailing list
>since Stanley is a member.

I don't know if this is really the place. I only=20
briefly mentioned the term in that interview=20
(along with livecoding btw), so it would be too=20
long to discuss here, methinks. "Abstract=20
Machine" is a complex term that has a historical=20
use (Deleuze & Guattari) as well as a=20
technological use (computer science), upon which=20
I glob my own definition. Rather than discussing=20
semantics and etymology here, I wonder if we=20
shouldn't have this discussion somewhere else so=20
as not to bother the livecoders. Of course I=20
would be willing to take a stab at answering your=20
question here, but this question does seem to=20
deal with something else altogether than=20
livecoding...
-- 
