out of curiosity, has anyone else read Hermann Hesse's Glass Bead Game book =

recently, interpreting it in the light of live coding?

Hermann Hesse The Glass Bead Game, Vintage: London 2000 translated by=20
Richard and Clara Winston.

P23 GBG as live coding, description of the game

>From stringing beads on wire to represent musical notation, =E2=80=98was =
taken=20
over by mathematicians.=E2=80=99

P23-4 =E2=80=98the players, mutually elaborating these processes, threw =
these=20
abstract formulas at one another, displaying the sequences and=20
possibilities of their science.=E2=80=99

Mnemonists spoil the game
P70 =E2=80=98talent without character, virtuosity without values=E2=80=99
introduce contemplation (spirituality)

Physicalist position p81 =E2=80=98someone who can read notes but has no =
command=20
of my instrument should not join in the dialogue on music.=E2=80=99

A public essay on algorithm. A disputation/dialectic.
P101, doubt of game. =E2=80=98It would be better not to play this Game, but =
to=20
occupy oneself with uncontaminated mathematics and good music.=E2=80=99




