Date: Tue, 18 Jul 2006 10:13:04 -0500
From: "Justin Sante" <jsante
Subject: Re: [livecode] wired online article


------=_Part_3311_993914.1153235584367
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1; format=flowed
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit
Content-Disposition: inline

Wired will do a proper story when there's someone or something to do it on.
That was more of a blurb.  If there were a big conference or a livecoder got
famous, they'd expend a lot more resources creating the article.

The best way to nurture our shared art/hobby is to let it grow organically
and on its own -- imposing a hierarchy from above is counter productive.

 - Justin.

