I'm new to this list, found you all via the Wired article.  I would
love to see some "how do I start?" articles up on the wiki.  "Hacking
perl in nightclubs" is a good read, but I felt might leave some
new-comers in the dust.  I have wanted to dive into Chuck or Fluxus,
but haven't had the time....perhaps some nice short tutorials,
(screencasts would be awesome!) on some of the basics.

Livecoding has a very bright future (IMHO), not just in the
performance/art space, but in computing in general.  I think you guys
are doing groundbreaking work, keep it up!


