From: Ge Wang <gewang
Subject: [livecode] ChucK / miniAudicle release (mac + linux + win)
Date: Wed, 26 Jul 2006 22:51:55 -0400



--Apple-Mail-1--432143840
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable
Content-Type: text/plain;
	charset=ISO-8859-1;
	format=flowed

Dear all,

The new miniAudicle, now for OS X, Linux, and Windows, have been
released (see notes below).  It's an integrated editor and ChucK virtual
machine, and provides syntax coloring and on-the-fly programming
control.  It's also a fun way to learn ChucK.

     http://audicle.cs.princeton.edu/mini/

More links from the toplap wiki:

     http://www.toplap.org/index.php/ChucK

Let us know of your thoughts, suggestions, and any questions.  Post
to the mailing lists (http://chuck.cs.princeton.edu/community/) or email
us.  The thing is still very experimental (especially on linux and=20
windows),
but can be a very useful companion/alternative to the classic command
line way of chuck coding.

Keep on ChucKin'...

Ge!

