Date: Mon, 07 Aug 2006 13:34:49 +0100
From: Nick Collins <nc272
Subject: Re: [livecode] Live Coding Practice



> I had to stop because I have to write my article on set theory. But maybe
> I can do another short session today. Will you upload new sessions?

uploading whenever I can, six days so far.

> yes, I'm pretty sure that'll be available soon.

easy to implement, even perhaps from the .document output? ah, yes, I see 
from your next line you're thinking the same way...

> I think it is better actually to get it from the .document format, which
> is more readeable. Maybe we should allow for one more digit in the time
> (10ms should be fine as haptic rate resolution?).

why not 1ms format anyway? Though there could be weird interactions based 
on sending time whatever we do, since waveform level sync not guaranteed 
without sendBundle/OffsetOut and originals won't often involve that.

haptic rate resolution is 15Hz ie 67 msec. Typing world record is 12 Hz 
(characters). But delaying and choosing when to press enter could have more 
resolution I guess!

N











