From: Adrian Ward <adrian
Subject: Re: [livecode] book
Date: Wed, 30 Aug 2006 14:41:43 +0100



On 28 Aug 2006, at 02:46, Andrew Brown wrote:

> On 28/08/2006, at 6:51 AM, douglas edric stanley wrote:
>
>> There was a very inspiring book a few years back by Friends of Ed  
>> called 4x4 Generative Design. Many a student wore the binding down  
>> on that one until it was just leaflets. You probably all know of  
>> it as Adrian Ward was one of the authors, (...)
>
> I think Friends of Ed would be a good publisher to approach. (...)

Yeah, Friends of Ed. Heh. They went bust. I don't think it was my  
fault. Anyway, they defaulted on the royalties.

Well, count me in if a book looks likely. Happy to contribute both  
content and editorial effort, and I do think it'd be worth it if we  
can think of an inspirational way to get round the 'a book is not a  
performance' hiccup. The 4x4 approach was fun because it broke the  
publisher's instructional expectations, instead it turned out to be  
speculative and a bit vague, verging on becoming a call for action.  
Combining technical gore with radical rhetoric is definitely a  
winning formula.

-- 
Ade



