From: Dylan McNamee <dylan
Subject: Re: [livecode] livecoding physics
Date: Thu, 23 Nov 2006 22:23:43 -0800



Related to physics-simulation-driven sound generation, I enjoyed  
playing around with balldroppings (http://jtnimoy.net/itp/ 
balldroppings)  a while ago, and hacked together my own related  
version in Java. It generates MIDI events driven by balls hitting  
paddles in a world with gravity.  I call it Kapwing.  Check it out on  
my page http://www.mecodegoodsomeday.com

cheers!
dylan


