if you are not depending on any ressources on the=20
server, you can quickly boot a new one if you=20
actually have managed to crash the old.

sclang is easy to crash with an infinite loop =E0=20
la: fork { loop { } } or anything that approaches=20
such a situation, but otherwise it usually is=20
pretty stable.

Alex, are you sending osc first to sclang and from there to scserver?

