Date: Mon, 27 Nov 2006 18:14:27 +0100
From: Kassen <signal.automatique
Subject: [livecode] Rule based intonation


------=_Part_92371_15800532.1164647667065
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1; format=flowed
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit
Content-Disposition: inline

http://www.speech.kth.se/music/performance/performance_rules.html

I chanced upon this link by accident but it seems relevant. It's about
various forms of musical intonation expressed in rules. This would be
interesting for any sort of music-related coding but perhaps especially for
livecoding where it could be said that the act of expressing the rules is
the intonation itself.

I would also be quite interested in similar resources that anyone might
know.

Yours,
Kas.

