Subject: Re: [livecode] Rule based intonation
From: alex <alex
Date: Mon, 27 Nov 2006 17:25:26 +0000


On Mon, 2006-11-27 at 18:14 +0100, Kassen wrote:
> http://www.speech.kth.se/music/performance/performance_rules.html
> 
> I chanced upon this link by accident but it seems relevant. It's about
> various forms of musical intonation expressed in rules. This would be
> interesting for any sort of music-related coding but perhaps
> especially for livecoding where it could be said that the act of
> expressing the rules is the intonation itself. 

Yes I gave this link here twice already the last week!

This paper has a  review of this area including some evalutation of KTH
rules:

Widmer, G. and Goebl, W. (2004). Computational Models of Expressive
Music Performance: The State of the Art. Journal of New Music Research
33(3), 203-216.
http://www.cp.jku.at/research/papers/Widmer_Journal_of_New_Music_Research.pdf

There are opensource implementations of the KTH rules available but I
haven't heard of anyone using them yet.

cheers

alex




