On 10 Jan 2007, at 16:08, Fredrik Olofsson wrote:

> i see live coding as performance art.  the artist(s) provoke and  
> involve the audience, make statements that confuse or muse.  just  
> happens that for many of us here there's a dac involved.

Yes, I'd agree with this. For me, livecoding isn't about the skill of  
musical performance so much as it is that doing so makes a statement  
that is integral to a creative agenda. After all, skill is an  
inherent part of any artistic endeavour (and whether the particular  
artist has skill or not is a different matter and is somehow  
irrelevant to this discussion).

Just my 2p...



