Subject: [livecode] drumming circle in london (uk) this sunday
From: alex <alex
Date: Fri, 26 Jan 2007 19:57:41 +0000



Sorry for the late notice, but I thought some livecoders in London would
be interested in the laptop drumming circle.  We're meeting this Sunday,
let me know if you're coming along.

Details follow...


OPENLAB LAPTOP DRUMMING CIRCLE

place: state51, 8-10 rhoda street
time: 2pm, sunday 28th jan
if you arrive late: phone 07976552375 to get in (or we won't hear you)

kind of a practice, although i guess there will be a lot of technical
set up time and testing of timing algorithms and protocols.

* no melodies (grey area - pitched drums are ok, but timbre is the
focus)
* no sequencers, algorithmic rhythms only!
* free software only (closed source o/s accepted)
* no real drums (unless robot controlled)

http://www.pawfal.org/openlab/index.php?page=LaptopDrummingCircle


Directions:

Find your way to where brick lane crosses bethnal green road.  The
number 8 and 388 buses, or the Liverpool street, Old street
or Bethnal Green tube stations should help.  (Note that shoreditch
station is now closed.)

Once there, grab yourself a tasty bagel from one of the local bagel
shops.  When ready, go north up brick lane until you see rhoda street on
your left.

Best viewed in a fixed width font:

    rhoda street
          |
        __V__| |___
        ___ _   ___
state51 -> * | |
         ____| |_____
         ____   _____-> bethnal green road
             | |
  bagels -> *| |
             | |
             |||
              V
           brick lane
              

state51 is on rhoda street, has 'state51' written on the gate in times
new roman. go up the metal stairs on the left hand side and knock on the
door.  unless you're late, in which case ring 07976552375.

cheers!

		




