From: Ge Wang <gewang
Subject: Re: [livecode] New to this
Date: Mon, 12 Feb 2007 01:54:59 -0500


Welcome Eric!!

> =A0=A0=A0I'm new to this list and new to live coding.=A0 I'm just =
curious what=20
> you experts would say is the best place for a newcomer like me to=20
> begin live coding?=A0 I'm reading up on ChucK and I have worked with=20=

> CSound, Max/MSP, and PD before.=A0 I'm not a programmer (yet) but I do=20=

> understand a little about how to program.=A0 My goal is to do live =
audio=20
> coding.=A0 I'm running a Linux (Ubuntu) OS and have lots of time to=20
> learn.=A0 Should I spend more time reading up on programming or on=20
> practicing/experimenting?=A0 Basically I'm looking for any pointers or=20=

> good howtos out there thanks.

I'm no expert, but I say start hacking/coding/playing!  Get comfortable=20=

in the languages and environments - even if you don't start out coding=20=

"live".  In fact, it may be more productive to learn the ins and outs=20
and nuances of the languages first, and develop your own sense of what=20=

it means to live code.

Also, while I'm glad you are looking into ChucK (for wholly biased=20
reasons), I'd additionally recommend checking out the wealth of live=20
coding systems out there, including SuperCollider, Impromptu (.98 just=20=

released a few hours ago), PERL or python based systems, etc:  here is=20=

a list:

     http://www.toplap.org/index.php/ToplapSystems

Most of the environments can take a little getting used to, or possibly=20=

more if you haven't programmed a lot before.  But that's part of the=20
process I reckon, and I think that's why it's good to do at least a=20
little every day or so.  Depending on your world view, there may be no=20=

wrong way to live code, or possibly no right way to live code.  The=20
best thing to do is to fire away.  Do some of everything, write code,=20
read, think about how you might turn your existing Csound, Max, or PD=20
environment into programming-driven meta-instruments, listen, code=20
more, share your code, start a live coding session with your=20
neighbor/friend/significant other...

Fire away.  Yeah?

Best,
Ge!



