Date: Mon, 12 Feb 2007 23:13:22 -0500
From: mcburton <mcburton
Subject: Re: [livecode] New to this


On 2/12/07, alex <alex@hiddenorg> wrote:
> Also I've heard a couple of experienced hackers (whose opinions I
> greatly respect) who have independently heaped praise upon the
> supercollider language itself.  This surprised me somewhat, it seems it
> is a very fine example of an object oriented language.

The Supercollider language is heavily based on Smalltalk, which is one
of those languages (like LISP) that was so awesome it hurt, but alas
was too far ahead of its time and never hit mainstream (many languages
like python and ruby still don't support all the sweet features)...

It makes the CS grad in me squeak with delight ;-)


Date: Tue, 13 Feb 2007 09:06:38 +0100
From: =?UTF-8?B?QXR0ZSBBbmRyw6kgSmVuc2Vu?= <atte.jensen
Subject: Re: [livecode] OT: simple emacs question


James Baker wrote:
> I know this is ot but im sure plenty of people on this list use emacs.
> Simple question, how do you select text without a mouse? (i.e. whats
> the C-? C-? etc)

The ones I use the most:

C-x h	select all
C-space start mark
A-w     copy between start mark an cursor to kill buffer
C-y     yank (=paste) from kill buffer
C-k     kill (cut) rest of line to kill-buffer

-- 
peace, love & harmony
Atte

http://www.atte.dk      | quintet:      http://www.anagrammer.dk
                         | compositions: http://www.atte.dk/compositions


