From: nescivi <nescivi
Subject: [livecode] Livecoding on the LAC
Date: Thu, 22 Feb 2007 17:14:13 +0100


Hi all,

As a perfect example of open source software, the Linux Audio Conference wi=
ll=20
feature a livecoding workshop, and concert, hosted by Powerbooks Unplugged=
=20
(adc and friends).
In addition, there will be many other interesting things on the conference,=
 so=20
hope to see you there!

below is the official press release.

sincerely,
Marije


The 5th Linux Audio Conference is taking place in Berlin (Germany) in 2007.=
=20
The TU-Berlin is hosting the conference in cooperation with people of the=20
Humboldt University Berlin, the Berliner K=FCnstlerprogramm of the DAAD, th=
e=20
festival MaerzMusik, the Instituto Cervantes Berlin and the Tesla Berlin.
The conference shows once per year important developments in the subject =A0
making music with Linux and open source tools. Invited is everyone who is=20
interested in the possibilities of this platform.=20
The LAC is offering a wide range of workshops, tutorials and hands on demos=
=2E=20
There will be presentations on the subjects Computer Music, Music Productio=
n,=20
Drivers and Sound Architectures and Audio Distributions.=20
The LAC aims at bringing together developers and users of Linux and=20
open source audio software with the goal of information sharing, project=20
discussion and music.=20
Each day of the conference there is a concert which features music composed=
=20
and created with open source software. One of the highlights of the confere=
nce=20
is the demonstration of a auditorium of the TU-Berlin, that has been equipp=
ed=20
with a new spatialisation system (Wave Field Synthesis), driven by a=20
Linux-Cluster.=20

The program of the conference is now online and (free) registration is=20
possible.

=46ree admission to all events except to the concerts at the Tesla and the=
=20
MaerzMusik=20
LAC2007 22.3. to 25.3.2007, TU-Berlin, www.lac.tu-berlin.de


