From: Andrew Sorensen <andrew
Subject: [livecode] Moxie?
Date: Sat, 3 Mar 2007 11:19:46 +1000



--Apple-Mail-1--843424935
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit
Content-Type: text/plain;
	charset=US-ASCII;
	delsp=yes;
	format=flowed

Hi All,

Does anyone on the list know of any live programming history relating  
to D.J.Collinge's Moxie computer music environment?  He seemed to be  
totally onto live programming as a performance practice pre 1984! but  
I can't find any specific information describing performances etc..   
I would love to hear from anyone who has any information about  
Moxie!  (My only links are Collinge's 1984 & 1988 ICMC papers which I  
traced back via Dannenberg's Moxc).

It appears that Impromptu has a great grandfather that I never knew  
about :)

Cheers,
Andrew.

p.s. If you haven't read the 1984 ICMC Moxie paper, definitely worth  
a look.

Collinge, D. J. MOXIE: A Language for Computer Music Performance. In.  
W. Buxton (editor), Proceedings of the International Computer Music  
Conference 1984
--Apple-Mail-1--843424935
Content-Transfer-Encoding: quoted-printable
Content-Type: text/html;
	charset=ISO-8859-1

