I've just uploaded an mp3 of last nights aa-cell performance.  The  
recording was taken straight from the desk so no typing noises (sorry  
Fredrik ;)  However, there was a video camera at the performance,  
which I assume had an inbuilt mic, so hopefully I can get my hands on  
a quicktime movie.

The performance goes for about 25 minutes and the file is about 28M.
http://homepage.mac.com/digego/aacell_at_the_loft.mp3

BTW:  Two DI boxes solved our usual projection hum problems.  So  
thanks to Adrian and Fredrik for a simple but effective solution ;)

Cheers,
Andrew.

Photo from the gig


