From: Nick Collins <nc272
Subject: [livecode] SuperCollider Symposium


[apologies for cross-postings]

SuperCollider Symposium and Courses
September 17 - 23, 2007

The Hague, The Netherlands

supported by: DCR, <tag>, The Institute of Sonology, STEIM,=20
SampleAndHold.org, The City of The Hague, Studio Loos, Theater Zeebelt

Beginners and Advanced Workshops
	September 17-19
	tutors: Nick Collins, Julian Rohrhuber, Jan Trutzschler and others to be=20
announced

Project Presentations, Lectures, Symposium Sessions and Developer Meetings=20
and Concerts
	September 20 - 22

Concerts:
	two concerts and a club night including a live-coding jam

Listening Room & Installations:
	During the week or the weekend.

Submission Deadline: June 18 2007
Notification of acceptance: June 24 2007

Call for presentations and performances

We are now accepting proposals for participation in the second=20
SuperCollider Symposium, in The Hague, The Netherlands. The Symposium will=20
introduce SuperCollider (SC) to new users, show the current state of=20
development and host talks and presentations of projects, in which SC plays =

an important role. In addition there will be concerts with music utilizing=20
the software. The concerts are open to the public.

Email short outlines of possible talks, workshops, projects and=20
performances (maximum 200 words) to the organisers below by June 18.

Composers and performers, who wish to submit pieces/performance ideas for=20
the concerts, should also send (if possible) links to web locations of=20
downloadable audio files, or mail CDs to the address below. For pieces and=20
performances the following options are available:
- tape pieces for the wavefield synthesis concert
- live electronic pieces with or without instruments or audio-visual=20
performances
- stereo tape pieces or recordings of live pieces for the listening room
- registration for the live coding jam/competition
- performances for the club night

We would be also happy to receive proposals for (sound) installations.=20
Regarding performances and installations we might be able to provide=20
players and/or financial help. Please contact us for more details.

Registration

Registration for the beginner's course and advanced workshops is on a first =

come first served basis; you should initially email the organisers below to =

reserve a place.

Course prices are: 120 =E2=82=AC (100 =E2=82=AC students) 3 day =
Beginners/Advanced=20
Course/Workshops

Participants will usually have their own laptops. However, a limited number =

of Macs will be available. Please specifically request if you will need a=20
computer provided. We are always happy to see Linux users, but we will not=20
compile your kernel for you, and will not provide Linux computers. Windows=20
is also an option (via PsyCollider) if you have your own machine (see=20
http://supercollider.sourceforge.net/).

Fees for attending the Symposium sessions: 55 =E2=82=AC (35 =E2=82=AC =
students).=20
Attendance will be free for anyone giving an advanced workshop.

Courses and Symposium: 145 =E2=82=AC (115 =E2=82=AC students)

For more information contact:
Jan Tr=C3=BCtzschler von Falkenstein
DCR
c/o Jan Tr=C3=BCtzschler
De Constant Rebequeplein 20B
NL- 2518 RA Den Haag
The Netherlands

Some accommodation options and other local information will be made=20
available shortly on the website below.


Email: sc.symposium.2007@hiddencom
http://superColliderSymposium.sampleAndHold.org/







