YES!  it's good; get it if you have any interest in end-user  
programming (of which I consider livecoding a cornerstone).

'The Humane Interface' by Jef Raskin is also interesting, especially  
with the renewed commercial interest in Zooming User Interfaces (e.g.  
iPhone / Core Animation, Microsoft's Photosynth and FTIR table called  
"Surface", etc.)

