Von: Georg Hajdu <georghajdu@hiddencom>
Datum: 13. August 2007 18:32:50 MESZ
An: maxmsp@hiddencom
Betreff: [maxmsp] Music in the Global Village Conference, September =20
6-8, Budapest, Hungary
Antwort an: maxmsp@hiddencom

Second Announcement (please forward to other lists and individuals)

The Hungarian Computer Music Foundation (HCMF) and the Hochschule f=FCr =20=

Musik und Theater Hamburg (HfMT) are proud to announce the Music in =20
the Global Village conference, the first international conference =20
dedicated exclusively to network music composition and performance to =20=

be held from September 6-8, 2007 in Budapest, Hungary.
There will be 20 lectures by leading experts in the field as well as =20
3 concerts with ensembles from Europe and the United States.

Invited speakers:
John Bischoff (keynote speaker, USA)
Chris Brown (USA)
Mark Trayle (USA)
Scot Gresham-Lancaster (USA)
Sergi Jord=E1 (E)
Julian Rohrhuber (D)
Alberto de Campo (A)
Nick Didkovsky (USA)
Anne La Berge (NL)
Johannes Kretz (A)
Georg Hajdu (D)
Andrea Szigetv=E1ri (H)
=C1d=E1m Siska (H)
Alex Car=F4t (D)
Karlheinz Essl (A)
J=F6rg Stelkens (D)
Marek Choloniewski (PL)
Anthony De Ritis (USA)
Mikl=F3s Petern=E1k (H)
Students of the master's program in multimedia composition at the =20
Hamburg School of Music and Theater

Invited musicians and ensembles:
The Hub (USA)
Powerbooks_unplugged (EU)
Extended Guitars (USA/EU)
Anne La Berge and Loos (NL)
European Bridges Ensemble (EU)
J=E1nos N=E9gyesy (USA)
Karlheinz Essl (A)

For a detailed conference schedule please refer to =20
www.globalvillagemusic.net.
Please send your inquiries to info@hiddennet
We are looking forward to seeing you in Hungary.

Georg Hajdu, Andrea Szigetv=E1ri and
the Music in The Global Village conference team

The conference is sponsored by Bipolar German-Hungarian cultural =20
projects - an initiative of the German Federal Cultural Foundation



