> search for some good settings if you send me the synthdef... it can
> iteratively update the settings as they improve - is that live coding??
> I need to get another paper out of it then I can GPL it.

I'd be really up for that.  The synthdef is using the Haskell client
libraries, I can send you that or try to duplicate it in sclang...  It's
a really simple patch anyway

I don't know if GAs can live code, maybe we can do the usual cop out and
call it artificial live coding. :)

cheers

artificial alex




