I very much enjoyed these, the range of techniques and aproaches keeps it
all exciting; wonderfull performances.

Listening to these was a bit like I felt as a child listening to the radio,
with the lack of visual cues giving a added sense of anticipation. Still, I
do think it would be good to give some thought to what form downloads of
livecoding performances should idealy take. I don't think there are ready
made formats for audio with sub-titles but that's roughly what I imagine
would be a interesting idea.

Yours,
Kas.

