Date: Wed, 22 Aug 2007 15:23:21 -0400
From: "Graham Coleman" <ravelite
Subject: Re: [livecode] Livecode recordings uploaded


------=_Part_37782_19317158.1187810601321
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=ISO-8859-1
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 7bit
Content-Disposition: inline

Kas,

Supercollider seems to have a system for logging the code that goes to the
server, the History class. In so far as you could use that to re-render a
performance, you could potentially render it to some video format. Fredrik
has already posted some of his history.

ChucK does not have a system for logging code sent to the VM, but I can see
no reason why something like that could not be added.

I think a screencast is a good format for this, but it's harder to do that
in actual live performance.

Andrew Sorenson has a good one here:
http://impromptu.moso.com.au/gallery.html

Graham

On 8/22/07, Kassen <signal.automatique@hiddencom> wrote:

