I'm up for London livecode too, if only to get hold of some of these=20
stickers...

The two ICMC live coding papers were from The Andrews, presented as a demo=20
with aa cell entertaining a succession of visitors:

08:40 [1498] - AA-CELL IN PRACTICE: AN APPROACH TO MUSICAL LIVE CODING
Andrew Sorensen, MOSO, Australia; Andrew Brown, Queensland University of=20
Technology, Australia

and

LIVE CODING: AN OVERVIEW
Iohannes zm=C3=B6lnig, Gerhard Eckel, Insitute of Electronic Music and=20
Acoustics, IEM, Austria

which is probably best described as a review paper summarising other papers =

pre 2007. What is heartening is that Iohannes is actually setting out on a=20
PhD in live coding!

I sold Miller Sm Puckette a TOPLAP CD, on the grounds that he saw Iohannes' =

presentation and liked slub. Unfortunately I had to miss it myself, being=20
at a soundcheck, else I could report more thoroughly on the presentation=20
itself. Iohannes, will you put it up online?

best,
N












