Date: Wed, 2 Jan 2008 14:51:04 +0100
From: douglas edric stanley <destanley
Subject: Re: [livecode] non-linguistic programming


I spoke about the subject of text-based=20
programming languages in my talk at "Art-Oriented=20
Programming 2" last October. It was one of my=20
principle objects-of-attack:

http://www.abstractmachine.net/blog/algorithmic-writing-systems/

To give some context to this talk, I was asked to=20
specifically address the subject of "languages".

Of note: I call them text-based languages because=20
I think (as I describe in the paper) that they=20
have very little to do with language, and have=20
everything to do with the way in which ASCII is=20
represented within the machine.

>I've just watched this excellent talk about how GUI widgets may be fused
>together in order to compose higher order behaviour:
>
>   http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3DfaJ8N0giqzw

Interesting talk. I love the part about fusion=20
and the discussion that follows on that subject.=20
It was exactly this type of thinking that I was=20
proposing in the above paper. More specifically,=20
I love how he answers the problem of code=20
analysis through his evocative narrative of a=20
video camera watching (someone's) behavior over=20
time. I think he gets to that narrative because=20
of the way he's looking at the problem: "I want=20
to stay in this world of concreteness and=20
directness, rather than going into this world of=20
abstraction and syntax as a very indirect way of=20
getting to meanings."

>Conal points to this book as inspiration:
>
>   http://www.alphabetvsgoddess.com/index.html

Oh my! Sounds like I'm stuck back in the 70's,=20
growing up in Northern California.

>You could construct a nasty diatribe against livecoding with this...
>Text as misogynistic, out of balance.  I wonder if there's anything in
>it?

I wouldn't pay much attention to that book, or=20
else just read between the lines for some=20
interesting ideas. But don't take it at face=20
value. There's some pretty scary street-feminism=20
in there by someone who doesn't seem to have done=20
their homework. I'm sure a case could be made for=20
any of the ideas he suggests, but even a mere=20
glance at his timeline... oh, bffftth!
-- 
