Date: Sat, 5 Jan 2008 01:54:22 +0100
From: douglas edric stanley <destanley
Subject: Re: [livecode] non-linguistic programming


After reading all the responses, I feel like I=20
should point out that the real crux of my=20
argument -- or the whole point of it if you will=20
-- was not to start any qualitative argument=20
about the good or bad of text based programming.=20
Especially on this list!

My qualification was merely a result of my=20
approach of looking at text-based programming=20
languages from the perspective of:

- the keyboard
- the ascii table
- the array
- the state register

This is far more interesting (to me at least)=20
than the ++ or -- of text-based programming, or=20
the relationship between natural languages and=20
programming languages which is one of the oldest=20
debates in the book; even if that old debate is=20
actually what Livecoding is playing with (in=20
part).

So the real argument for me was: why are=20
text-languages the most powerful forms for=20
programmable machines, and why do we keep coming=20
back to them? I think the above 4 conditions=20
frame the question in a revealing way (at least=20
for me).
-- 
