Date: Sat, 5 Jan 2008 02:01:13 +0100
From: douglas edric stanley <destanley
Subject: Re: [livecode] non-linguistic programming


On the subject of knitting, I just noticed this. Maybe someone 
already mentioned it already?

http://www.we-make-money-not-art.com/archives/009872.php#comments

There are of course a million different things going on right now 
with knitting. Machine Projects did some workshops some time back, as 
have many others.

And yes, the Jacqard Loom was my original reference. I don't see much 
of what we do these days as all that different from Jacqard Looms. At 
least not mechanically. I suppose the level of abstraction is a 
little too specified, but even there...

...

On the subject of livecoding interfaces other than keyboards, my 
Rubik's Cube controller was originally designed for Livecoding. It 
quickly turned into a simple 6-track midi sequencer but that wasn't 
the original intention. I suppose I should make some more digestible 
demos of how that aspect worked...
