On 1/5/08, AlgoMantra <algomantra@hiddencom> wrote:
>
>
> > what's the difference between code and sequencing?
> >
>
> IMHO - a sequence is its own meaning, but code 'means
> into being' another sequence.

i should have said "coding (programming universal machines) and
sequencing (programming particular class of machines)

or "code or sequencer score".

my answer would be: sequencer is a particular case of programmable
machines and sequencer score is a particular class of code.

