I don't see how that disagrees with my statement.

I didn't say all of the social reality is now magically moved to
computer-based medium, I leave that to Matrix-conspiracy-theorists.

It's more like http://www.flickr.com/photos/artm/2185389392/ (I didn't
mean sizes to reflect anything, just don't have much space at the moment
to make show the picture in perspective. And I wanted Shiva to stay
"readable" :)

My email client that you see on a laptop screen could be showing Russian
or Arabic text, about Indian culture or African mythology. But i could
make Shiva mean Jesus Christ, now could I?

Neither voltage levels not magnetic properties of harddrives nor use of
binary code to represent numbers are culture specific (well, OK, binary
code could be traced to India I guess) and the fact that so much of them
are used to *REPRESENT* anglophone/western artefacts just reflects the
state of the world, but isn't innate to computers.

And I see what you argue, it's just that I don't agree that your
argument contradicts mine :)

My keyboard only has english("latin") letters on it and i don't have to
configure them because i prefer english versions of my OSes.

... but need to distract myself from this thread and reflect some ...

