I think that the beauty of visual programming languages are that the
contraints are obvious in that they are visible. Obvious contraints make
for creative environments, because you don't need to second guess what is
going on behind the scenes - you don't even need to think about it.

I think the way starlogo deals with a pretty complex syntax is interestin=
g
in that it's obvious what can go where because they are shaped
differently:
http://education.mit.edu/starlogo/

