>
> There are many branches of mathematics. Sound synthesis languages are a
> mathematics of sound, which have to take into account that the being of
> sound is more than its waveform. Just as any mathematics, it is not trivial
> to describe something formally. 'Low level' system commands may well turn
> out to be less mathematical than 'high level' programming languages. Despite
