I think many times when I follow a mathematical derivation, or proof,
I have  felt that it was a sort of code stirring visualizations in my head.
As I continue to believe (perhaps wrongly) - we have surrounded ourselves
by walls of categories that shouldn't exist in the first place. Math and
code
are pretty much the same to me, and there are moments when sound is
image, and vice versa. I don't believe I'm talking to a screen right now.

Now Master Kassen will say that "but categories are useful", and "they help
us
organise our thoughts in a constructive way". Of course he's right, but
I persist...:)

