Date: Tue, 06 May 2008 10:28:01 -0700
From: Craig Latta <craig
Subject: Re: [livecode] audio games



Hi Kas--

      I've made some progress on Quoth; it had been using Squeak device 
drivers that were Windows-specific, but after my Windows laptop died I 
rewrote them using Port[Audio,MIDI], which runs on several host 
platforms. I presented Quoth running on a Powerbook to the Bay Area 
Computer Music Technology group from meetup.com a few months ago.

      I'm working on a release of Squeak which will make Squeak 
application deployment reasonable, for 2008-06-20 (solstice), and a 
Quoth release for 2008-09-22 (equinox).


      thanks!

-C

-- 
Craig Latta
improvisational musical informaticist
www.netjam.org
Smalltalkers do: [:it | All with: Class, (And love: it)]



Date: Tue, 06 May 2008 10:34:17 -0700
From: Craig Latta <craig
Subject: [livecode] the loud objects



      I saw these guys play at the Maker Faire last weekend, they were 
great. Live circuit building on an overhead projector, smoke rising from 
soldering irons, great visual appeal, some music I liked even came out. :)

      http://loudobjects.com


-C

-- 
Craig Latta
improvisational musical informaticist
www.netjam.org
Smalltalkers do: [:it | All with: Class, (And love: it)]


