Now that's a nice example of musical data-compression! The final word in
those unpleasant compressed-audio-format wars!

Which reminds me of this;
http://fora.tv/2006/06/26/Will_Wright_and_Brian_Eno

That's a talk between Will Wright (Spore) and Brian Eno which goes into many
aspects of generative systems, amongst other things data compression. Might
well be interesting/stimulating to list members, even if most of it
approaches generative systems from very different angles from what is
typically done here.

Yours,
Kas.

