I took the AVI route.

Looks nice, I liked how it comes across as quite simple yet very "playable";
of the livecoding performances I saw and downloaded so far this strikes me
as the closest to traditional musicianship I've seen yet but I can't quite
place my finger on why this is exactly. Might be the relation between the
(apparent) simplicity of the system and the continuity of the editing.

Looks very accessible as well, both towards the performer and the audience.

Thanks for posting this!

Kas.

