From: ToneText GmbH <tonetext
Date: Mon, 11 Aug 2008 21:40:07 +0200
Subject: [livecode] CALL FOR SHORT STEREOPHONIC SOUNDSCAPE & HOERSPIEL WORKS


CALL FOR SHORT STEREOPHONIC SOUNDSCAPE & HOERSPIEL WORKS

 >A DIAMOND IN THE MUD<
A Miniature Audio Exhibition of Stereophonic Soundscape & H=F6rspiel =
Works

PROJECT CONCEPT:
It is an Asian concept rooted in Buddhism that self-cultivation can be =20=

developed at home as a householder and is not merely confined to a =20
temple or monastery. Buddhist believe that enlightened beings are =20
those who "grew" out of the "mud" of the material world. So, like the =20=

lotus flower, which penetrates through sullied mud and water, but =20
emerges unspoiled, enlightened beings are beautiful and pure even =20
though they grow up in the material world. The phrase "a diamond in =20
the mud" is an analogy for this and in keeping with it the Digital Art =20=

Weeks would like to issue this call to artists and to submit pre =20
recorded works (Soundscape, H=F6rspiel, Poetry) in regard to the =20
beautiful and the sullied. The works will be chosen on their ability =20
to transcend the listeners into a "moment of tranquilly" and out of =20
the confines of the everyday, or as expressed in the Diamond Sutra: =20
"Dwell upon nothing and produce the pure mind."

PLAYBACK SYSTEM:
Constructed as a dock for Apple's famed iPod, the iCarta stereophonic =20=

audio playback system will be used to play back all of the selected =20
works. The systems not only offers an interesting solution for public =20=

pod-casting, but it also acts uniquely as a bathroom dispenser for the =20=

indispensable: Le papier toilette.

- Art Clay, DAW, Artistic Director (c) 2008


DEADLINE: Moday, 15th September 2008. Notification of acceptance of =20
proposals will be sent out on or before Monday, 22nd September 2008.

APLLICATION FORM:
http://www.digitalartweeks.ethz.ch/web/DAWPlus/SoundScape08

For more information regarding the call please write directly to: =
arthurclay@hiddencom=20
; for more on past Digital Art Weeks, please see: =
www.digitalartweeks.ethz.ch=20
; for technical information on the iCarta, please see: =
http://www.atechflash.com=


