<div dir="ltr"><br><div class="gmail_quote">On Wed, Sep 17, 2008 at 11:54 AM, krgn <span dir="ltr">&lt;<a href="mailto:k.gebbert@hiddencom">k.gebbert@hiddencom</a>&gt;</span> wrote:<br><blockquote class="gmail_quote" style="border-left: 1px solid rgb(204, 204, 204); margin: 0pt 0pt 0pt 0.8ex; padding-left: 1ex;">
<div dir="ltr">it must be something in the range of complexity described in Permutation City by Greg Egan :-)<br>a really nice SF book about automata, although I agree with someone I talked to about it that it gets confusing/confused in the end. but maybe thats the point...</div>
