>
> I started out calmly while people walked in with sonifying my keyboard
> presses which I thought would place more emphasis on the text being the
> interface to the sound for random passers by.
>

I saw this in a movie called Avalon by Mamoru Oshii. The fictional computer
they show in it has all the keypresses sonified. It's like the keyboard
becomes a sort of tabla.

http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Avalon_(Japanese_film)

